This paper deals with the optimization of offloading cellular traffic through opportunistic communications, which involves the analysis of network dissemination and the design of an adaptive algorithm. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including network infrastructure (cs.NI), social and information networks (cs.SI), information theory (cs.IT), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on wireless communication and mobility patterns, we believe that cs.NI and cs.SI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.IT, cs.CR, and cs.MM.
